You know what - there are a few things that have been bugging me lately


Like what happend to chivalry - or true love - or family and friends before work and yourself


Has everyone lost their fucking minds?!?!


I cant even begin to count the amount of times that i have seen the act of chivalry thrown aside - it sickens me that i dont see any men giving up their seat for a standing lady - or holding a door open for a woman with bags or a stroller - has everyone just given up on that kind of stuff - is money, good looks, and fame all anyone ever thinks about now a days? its getting kind of sad when the medieval times treated their women better than we do - granted women have changed as well - chivalry should not be dead.

Raise your hand if your one of the countless number of people that uses the phrase "I love you." every day - now raise your hand if you mean it - now i beleive whole heartedly that those three words should never be used unless you truly mean it - unfortuantly in this day and age more and more people seem to take those words for granted - when you say it to get someone to do something for you - when you say it just to make someone feel better - when you say it and are just playing with the person for shits and giggles - thats all i see now a days - couples are the worst - it used to be that those three simple little words used to be nothing simple at all - it used to be that when you said it you meant it and it was a long time before you said it to the one you were dating - now thats all i hear out of couples is "i love you" this and "i love you" that after dating eachother for a good day or two - then what do you know - about a week later their completly seperated dating other people with nothing to say of eachother but "i never wanted to date her/him" or "i hate him/her" - to me true love exists almost as much as my pet raptor, Gearald, that lives in my closet - sure there is true love out there somewhere but i havnt found it yet and i doubt i will.

And another thing - kind of going bak to the whole chivalry topic - people need to take time to help others - come on people - how hard is it to go out of your way for someone - to give up something of your own for someone else - whether it be time or possesions it shouldnt matter - this whole fucking planet needs a wake up call - if you cant give up five seconds to help someone out then you dont deserve any help from anyone else - unfortunately there are some people out there that really do give up tim and possesions just to be walked all over - not thanked not given anything in return - just taken for granted all that they do - when the person is chivalrous and gives up possesions for others - why is it that one person has the hardest time finding true love? why is it the one person who deserves to be truely loved has nothing - should the world just go back to ignoring eachother - will everyone be happier if the good ones stoped carring - or would it be that when the ones who care stop carring that the ones that take advantage of them will be completly and hopelessly lost - and will wish for them back.


Im just having a hard time seeing reality - whether or not i should give up trying to be the kind of guy that barely exists.






Well??

so yeah i have this really long story to tell you.....





















life blows.....



















end of story.
